**Windows 7 (2009)**

* Released: 2009
* Based on NT 6.1 kernel
* Editions: Starter, Home Basic, Home Premium, Professional, Ultimate, Enterprise
* Focused on performance, stability, and usability
* Improved taskbar with pinning and previews
* Faster boot and shutdown compared to Vista
* Better driver support and hardware compatibility
* Improved networking and homegroup features
* Strong compatibility with older Windows software
* Lower system requirements than Vista

**Professional notes:**

* Widely adopted in business and home environments
* Considered one of the most stable Windows versions
* Long-term support made it a standard in enterprises
* Still used today in legacy systems and virtual machines
